<br>
[The Good!]<br>
<br>
-It doesn't take 3-4 months to get one level.  After a solid 6 hours in the Hobgoblin group in PoN, I was able to churn up 40% experience at level 57.  The experience is a godsend instead of long horrid exp grinds.<br>
<br>
-I created the Magician to be the most powerful pet master.  Maybe I should have created a Beastlord, but I love the Wizard aspect of the magician as well, which is dealing hordes of damage.  PoP pets excite me!  Looking forward to level 60 @#%$ to summon and owning virtually anything I want in the old world is something I look forward to every single day.<br>
<br>
-The big nukes.  At level 44, I received a major nuking upgrade.  That was about the last major nuke upgrade I've gotten.  Now I use Shock of Steel, which although is nice, is only about 150-200 points average more damage than the level 44 nuke.  Oh the days where I start dishing out 2000 damage in one nuke...can't wait for em'!!<br>
<br>
-With the extra 5 levels, Verant balanced A LOT of the classes in respect to the game.<br>
<br>
[The Bad]<br>
<br>
-The Fire pet.  Oh Gawd, why oh why does Verant insist on keeping this style pet?  It's so bloody useless it's not even funny.<br>
<br>
-Charm?  Powerful, yes, but not what I envisioned the mage as.  If I wanted charm, I would have rolled an enchanter.  You guys know what I mean.<br>
<br>
-Seems like we get a lot of wasted AA...<br>
<br>
[The Ugly]<br>
<br>
-Ten thousand of the dumbest, wasteful, idiotic purple assed babboons are jammed into the same damn zones.  Verant made the experience so good in the planes that they didn't think to balance out some of the old world in comparison.  Smart business move on Verants part.  This gives incentive for crackfiends like me to buy the expansion, but poor on a game developement part.  You can practically skip expansions if you want to.  You'll just know that 6 months later when the next expansion is released that you'll never go back there again.  Hey, that's gas money!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
-With every expansion, Verant changes the main &quot;focus&quot; of raid/exp oriented groups.<br>
<br>
Kunark - DPS<br>
Velious - CH Chain<br>
Luclin - Strategy<br>
PoP - Debuffs (Slows, Cripple, etc)<br>
<br>
-All the [morons] in the same zone...<br>
<br>
-All the [morons] in the same zone...<br>
<br>
-All the [morons] in the same zone...<br>
<br>
-All the [morons] in the same zone...<br>
<br>
<br>
You get my drift. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
